(firstQuint)Virtual Reality a Novel Screening and Treatment Aid in Attention Deficit Disorder.

 Virtual Reality is a novel program designed to imitate a real classroom environment including various distractions.

 It includes a head monitor to track eye movements Children aged 10-20 years with ADHD will use the program with and without methylphenidate(1 mg/kg).

 Their results will be compared to a control group.

 Parental consent will be obtained.

